*php-7.0.1 (18 Dec 2015)

  18 Dec 2015; Brian Evans <grknight@gentoo.org> metadata.xml,
  +php-7.0.1.ebuild:
  Version bump including phpdbg support

  Package-Manager: portage-2.2.26

  07 Jan 2016; Michael Orlitzky <mjo@gentoo.org> -php-7.0.0.ebuild:
  remove php-7.0.0; use php-7.0.1 instead.

  Package-Manager: portage-2.2.24

  07 Jan 2016; Michael Orlitzky <mjo@gentoo.org> php-7.0.1.ebuild:
  update the apache2 post-install notification about mod_php.

  Newer versions of app-eselect/eselect-php require some apache
  configuration changes. This configuration is mentioned in the
  dev-lang/php pkg_postinst() phase, which isn't ideal, but is what it
  is. Since php:7.0 requires the new eselect-php, the pkg_postinst() for
  php:7.0 has been updated to reflect the configuration changes.

  Thanks to Tomáš Mózes for pointing this out.

  Gentoo-Bug: 552156

  Package-Manager: portage-2.2.24

